<inglise> A Community action entitled "European Capital of Culture" shall be established. </inglise>
<eesti> Kehtestatakse &uuml;henduse meede nimetusega "Euroopa kultuuripealinn". </eesti>
<inglise> Its objective shall be to highlight the richness and diversity of European cultures and the features they share, as well as to promote greater mutual acquaintance between European citizens. </inglise>
<eesti> Meetme eesm&auml;rk on esile t&otilde;sta Euroopa kultuuride rikkust ja mitmekesisust ning &uuml;hisjooni, samuti aidata kaasa Euroopa kodanike paremale tutvumisele &uuml;ksteisega. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 2 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 2 </eesti>
<inglise> 1. </inglise>
<eesti> 1. </eesti>
<inglise> One city of a Member State shall be designated as European Capital of Culture, in turn, as set out in Annex I. The chronological order set out in Annex I may be altered by mutual agreement between the Member States concerned. </inglise>
<eesti> Iga liikmesriigi &uuml;ks linn nimetatakse j&auml;rjekorras Euroopa kultuuripealinnaks, nagu I lisas s&auml;testatud. I lisas s&auml;testatud kronoloogilist j&auml;rjekorda v&otilde;ib muuta asjaomaste liikmesriikide omavahelisel kokkuleppel. </eesti>
<inglise> The nomination or nominations shall be notified to the European Parliament, the Council, the Commission and the Committee of the Regions by the Member State concerned, possibly accompanied by a recommendation from the latter, no later than four years before the event in question is due to begin. </inglise>
